Purchase options and add-ons

  • Superior Shielding Effect Our Faraday Fabric is crafted from top quality materials, including polyester, copper, and nickel, all combined into a thin 0.1 mm layer. This exceptional composition provides excellent conductivity, shielding effectiveness, and thermal conductivity. In addition, the Faraday cloth excels at effectively blocking a wide range of signals, boasting an impressive 99% blocking capability in the frequency range from 10kHz to 30GHz.
  • Versatile Applications Our Faraday Fabric finds a wide range of uses in EMI prevention, safeguarding business confidentiality, and ensuring personal privacy and security. This versatile fabric is perfect for crafting signal-shielded rooms (WiFi, GPS, Bluetooth, RFID, etc.), wall coverings, tower EMF shields, smart meter EMI shields, wireless router covers, anti-credit card skimming wallets, anti-theft car key fob bags, passport holders, phone pouches, and laptop protective bags.
  • Convenient & Easy to UseCopper fabric is a soft, lightweight material that's a breeze to work with.. Each fabric sheet measures 44 inches in width by 36 inches in length (approximately. 91m x 1.1m), offering 11 sq. ft. (1.22 sq. yds.) of versatile shielding material. All it takes is a simple cut and the use of tape for enhanced adhesion, and you can effortlessly create your own faraday cage and faraday bags emp proof regardless of your experience.
  • Safety and ProtectionOur Faraday fabrics is conductive, ensuring reliability. Be aware that it is flammable, so keep it away from electrical sources, outlets, plugs, and cables to reduce the fire risk.We are committed to providing high quality emf blockers for home that protect your health and privacy. Opting for our fabric is a responsible choice that enhances the privacy and well-being of your loved one.
  • Thoughtful Gift & User SupportIn a world where privacy and security concerns are on the rise, a thoughtful gift of Faraday Fabric for your loved ones is a thoughtful choice.. Help them safeguard their personal information and bid farewell to potential hackers. And should you encounter any questions or concerns, our dedicated support team is always here to assist you. Your peace of mind is our priority.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

  • D E
    5.0 out of 5 stars Decent metallized fabric
    Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
    Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    People don't think electromagnetic propagation be like it is, but it do. I will admit that the uses I put this fabric through were not as thorough as some of the other fabric testing I've done. This sheet will likely be included as part of a sandwich structure with oriented carbon fiber layers all set in epoxy in a heated hydraulic press. It will most likely be added to some more additional materials to add structural properties before being fully qualified in an EMC test rig. In a fast & loose test bed (that is, not clamped in a rig, and not "proper" protocol) in an anechoic chamber, I was getting ~ 50-60dB worth of attenuation, mostly from surface reflection over the 0.5 to 8GHz range. If you plan to use this to make shielding, there are several design rules that need to be met. No seams. No holes. No penetrations. Lapped joints. Openings should be rolled and secured. This fabric is fairly soft and flexible, and will need a protective layer to prevent any abrasion from creating aperture antennae that can amplify signals.
    Read more
